950/http://www.canterbury.ac.uk/salomons-museum/tree/d-lionel-salomons.asp |archivedate=28 September 2007 }}</ref> scientist and inventor\n* [[Jeffrey Goldstone]]<ref>JYB 2005 p214</ref>\n* [[Ian Grant (physicist)|Ian Grant]]<ref>JYB 2005 p214</ref>\n* Sir [[Peter Hirsch]], physicist<ref>JYB 2005 p213, 214</ref>\n* [[Herbert Huppert]], 1987<ref>JYB 2005 p214</ref>\n* [[Brian David Josephson]],<ref name=\"jewishvirtuallibrary1\"/> physicist, 1973 Nobel Prize \n* [[George Kalmus]], 1988<ref>JYB 2005 p214</ref>\n* [[Andrew Keller]]<ref>[https://archive.today/20121223075320/http://www.royalsoc.ac.uk/DServe/dserve.exe?dsqIni=Dserve.ini&dsqApp=Archive&dsqCmd=show.tcl&dsqDb=Persons&dsqPos=26&dsqSearch=((text)='jewish') ]</ref>\n* [[Olga Kennard]], crystallographer 1987<ref>JYB 2005 p214</ref>\n* [[Rudolf Kompfner]],<ref>[[Concise Dictionary of National Biography]]: \"born of Jewish parents in Vienna\"</ref> invented the [[traveling wave tube]]\n* [[Hans Kronberger (physicist)|Hans Kronberger]],<ref>Concise Dictionary of National Biography: \"born in Linz, Austria, of Jewish parents\"</ref> nuclear physicist\n* [[Nicholas Kurti]],<ref>[http://www.oup.co.uk/pdf/0-19-924108-2.pdf ]{{dead link|date=January 2016}}</ref> physicist, Vice-President of the Royal Society 1965-67  <ref>Oxford [[Dictionary of National Biography]]: \"study at the university was open to him, despite being a Jew ... Kurti became a naturalized British citizen just before the outbreak of the Second World War\"</ref>\n* [[Frederick Lindemann, 1st Viscount Cherwell]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://jewish-sci-tech-books.com/personalities.htm |accessdate=16 November 2006 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061019155142/http://www.jewish-sci-tech-books.com/personalities.htm |archivedate=19 October 2006 }}</ref> physicist and politician\n* [[Henry Lipson]]<ref>JYB 1990 p201</ref>\n* Sir [[Ben Lockspeiser]]<ref>JYB 1990 p201</ref>\n* [[Stanley Mandelstam]]<ref>JYB 2005 p214</ref>\n* [[Kurt Mendelssohn]]<ref>[[Encyclopaedia Judaica]] 13:492</ref>\n* [[Leon Mestel]], astronomer<ref>Who's Who entry & JYB 2000 p211</ref>\n* [[F.R. Nunes Nabarro]]<ref>JYB 2005 p214</ref>\n* [[Rudolf Peierls]]<ref>JYB 1995 p193</ref>\n* [[Michael Pepper]]<ref>JYB 2005 p214</ref>\n* [[Joseph Rotblat|Sir Joseph Rotblat]],<ref>[http://www.pugwash.org/publication/obits/obit-rotblat-press-latimes.ht ]{{dead link|date=January 2016}}</ref>physicist, 1995 Nobel Peace Prize \n* [[Adolf Schallamach]], physics of friction and wear of rubber\n* Sir [[Arthur Schuster]]<ref>[[Encyclopedia Judaica]], 14:1012</ref>\n* [[Dennis William Sciama|Dennis Sciama]], [[Royal Society|FRS]],<ref name=\"jinfo1\"/> cosmologist\n* [[David Shoenberg]], physics of low temperatures (JYB 1995 p193)\n* Sir [[Francis Simon]]<ref>[[Encyclopedia Judaica]], 14:1578</ref>\n* [[David Tabor]]<ref>JYB 2005 p214</ref>\n* [[Samuel Tolansky]], spectroscopist<ref>Concise Dictionary of National Biography: \"son of Lithuanian-Jewish immigrants\"</ref>\n* [[Felix Weinberg]]<ref>JYB 2005 p214</ref>\n* [[Michael Woolfson]], crystallographer, computer simulation 1984<ref>JYB 2005 p214</ref>\n* [[Alec David Young]], aero-engineer<ref>JYB 2005 p214</ref>\n* [[John Ziman]]<ref name=\"jinfo1\"/>\n\n==Chemists==\n<!--PLEASE DO NOT ADD ANY MORE NAMES TO THIS PAGE WITHOUT INCLUDING A CREDIBLE SOURCE FOR THE INFORMATION. SEE [[WIKIPEDIA:VERIFIABILITY]] AND [[WIKIPEDIA:NO ORIGINAL RESEARCH]], WHICH ARE POLICY. THE SOURCE MUST SAY THAT THE PERSON IS ACTUALLY JEWISH.-->\n\n* [[Herbert C. Brown|Herbert Brown]], chemist, 1979 Nobel Prize<ref name=\"JYB 2005 p215\">JYB 2005 p215</ref>\n* Sir [[Arnold Burgen]]<ref>JYB 2005 p214</ref>\n* Sir [[Roy Calne]]<ref>JYB 2005 p214</ref>\n* [[Jack David Dunitz]],<ref name=\"jinfo2\">{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.jinfo.org/Chemists.html |title=Jewish Chemists |website=Jinfo.org |date=1992-10-14 |accessdate=2016-01-22}}</ref> chemist\n* [[Martin Fleischmann]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nndb.com/people/452/000044320/ |title=Martin Fleischmann |website=Nndb.com |date= |accessdate=2016-01-22}}</ref> chemist\n* [[Rosalind Franklin]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jewishvirtuallibrary.org/jsource/biography/franklin.html |title=Rosalind Franklin |publisher=Jewish Virtual Library |date= |accessdate=2016-01-22}}</ref> [[Physical chemistry|physical chemist]] and [[Crystallography|crystallographer]], helped discover the structure of [[DNA]]\n* [[Eugen Glueckauf]]<ref>JYB 1980 p182</ref>\n* Sir [[Ian Heilbron]]<ref>[[Encyclopedia Judaica]] 8:262</ref>\n* [[Walter Heitler]]<ref name=\"jinfo2\"/>\n* [[Aaron Klug|Sir Aaron Klug]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nobelprize.org/chemistry/laureates/1982/klug-autobio.html |title=Aaron Klug - Biographical |website=Nobelprize.org |date= |accessdate=2016-01-22}}</ref> physicist and chemist, 1982 Nobel Prize<ref>JYB 2000 p211-2</ref>\n* [[Harold Kroto]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ca.geocities.com/wery_333tom/kroto-autobio.html |title=Sir Harold Kroto : Autobiography |website=Webcitation.org |accessdate=2016-01-22 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060507131843/http://ca.geocities.com/wery_333tom/kroto-autobio.html |archivedate=7 May 2006 |df=dmy }}</ref> discoverer of [[buckminsterfullerene]], 1996 Nobel Prize (Jewish father; raised Jewish)\n* [[Raphael Meldola]]<ref>[[Encyclopaedia Judaica]] 11:1290</ref>\n* [[Alfred Mond]], chemist <ref>[[Encyclopaedia Judaica]] 4:1298, 12:241</ref>\n* [[Ludwig Mond]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ajr.org.uk/pastjournal22.htm |title=AJR |website=AJR.org.uk |accessdate=2016-01-22}}</ref> chemist and industrialist\n* Sir [[Robert Mond]], chemist and archaeologist<ref>[[Encyclopaedia Judaica]], art. ''Mond''</ref>\n* [[Albert Neuberger]], <ref name=\"jinfo3\">{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.jinfo.org/Biomedical_Scientists.html |title=Jewish Biomedical Scientists |website=Jinfo.org |date=1992-10-14 |accessdate=2016-01-22}}</ref> chemical pathologist; father of Prof. [[James N