 England]] economist\n* [[Noreena Hertz]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jewishartsfest.org/index.cfm?page=single.cfm&sectionid=226 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20030425151954/http://www.jewishartsfest.org/index.cfm?page=single.cfm&sectionid=226 |archivedate=2003-04-25 |title=Jewish Arts Festival 2003 |date=2003-04-25 |accessdate=2016-01-22}}</ref> economist and activist\n* [[Richard Kahn, Baron Kahn]],<ref name=\"jinfo economists\">{{cite web|author=JINFO |url=http://www.jinfo.org/Economists.html |title=Jewish Economists |website=Jinfo.org |date=2009-12-06 |accessdate=2016-01-22}}</ref> economist: [[multiplier (economics)|multiplier]]\n* [[Nicholas Kaldor]],<ref name=\"jinfo economists\"></ref> economist\n* [[Michael Kidron]], [[South Africa]]n born Marxist economist, writer, cartographer and publisher\n* [[Israel Kirzner]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fff.org/freedom/0400f.asp |accessdate=21 March 2007 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070310070921/http://www.fff.org/freedom/0400f.asp |archivedate=10 March 2007 }}</ref> economist (UK-born)\n* [[Ludwig Lachmann]], economist<ref>Hayek's Challenge: An Intellectual Biography of F. A. Hayek - Pg 145</ref>\n* [[Harold Laski]], economist<ref>The New Standard Jewish Encyclopedia, ed Geoffrey Wigoder, 5th ed 1977, p 1182\u20133</ref>\n* [[Alexander Nove]], economist<ref>JYB 1990 p202</ref>\n* [[Sigbert Prais]], economist<ref name=\"JYB 2005 p215\"></ref>\n* [[David Ricardo]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cepa.newschool.edu/het/profiles/ricardo.htm |accessdate=21 March 2007 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070315092648/http://cepa.newschool.edu/het/profiles/ricardo.htm |archivedate=15 March 2007 }}</ref> economist (converted to Quakerism)\n* [[Arthur Seldon]],<ref>{{cite web|author=Alfred Sherman |url=http://politics.guardian.co.uk/politicsobituaries/story/0,1441,1590862,00.html |title=Obituary: Arthur Seldon &#124; Business &#124; The Guardian |website=Politics.g