22}}</ref> physicist, Nobel Prize 1954 (converted to [[Lutheranism]])<ref>JYB 2000 p212 - list of Jewish Nobel Prizewinners</ref>\n* [[Samuel Devons]], physicist<ref>JYB 2005 p214</ref>\n* [[Cyril Domb]],<ref name=\"jinfo1\"/> physicist, President of Association of Orthodox Jewish Scientists\n* [[Paul Eisler]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.totallyjewish.com/entertainment/features_and_reviews/?content_id=293 |accessdate=16 November 2006 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20050523191553/http://www.totallyjewish.com/entertainment/features_and_reviews/?content_id=293 |archivedate=23 May 2005 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.dundee.ac.uk/~gjzcallo/pcb%20manufacture.ppt ]{{dead link|date=January 2016}}</ref> inventor of the [[printed circuit board]]\n* [[Michael Fisher]]<ref name=\"jinfo1\"/>\n* [[Otto Robert Frisch]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nndb.com/people/119/000099819/ |title=Otto Robert Frisch |website=Nndb.com |date= |accessdate=2016-01-22}}</ref><ref>JYB 1980 p182</ref>\n* [[Herbert Frohlich]]<ref>JYB 1990 p201</ref>\n* [[Dennis Gabor]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ejewish.info/resources/resourceCategoryDisplay.aspx?categoryid=370&rsid=96 |accessdate=16 November 2006 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060716191944/http://www.ejewish.info/resources/resourceCategoryDisplay.aspx?categoryid=370&rsid=96 |archivedate=16 July 2006 }}</ref><ref name=\"jewishvirtuallibrary1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.jewishvirtuallibrary.org/jsource/Judaism/nobels.html |title=Jewish Nobel Prize Laureates |publisher=Jewish Virtual Library |date= |accessdate=2016-01-22}}</ref><ref>Oxford [[Dictionary of National Biography]]: \"In 1946 Dennis Gabor became a naturalized British citizen.\"</ref>  Nobel Prize for Physics 1971\n* Sir [[David Lionel Goldsmid-Stern-Salomons]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.canterbury.ac.uk/salomons-museum/tree/d-lionel-salomons.asp |accessdate=21 March 2007 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070928020950/http://www.canterbury.ac.uk/salomons-museum/tree/d-lionel-salomons.asp |archivedate=28 September 2007 }}</ref> scientist and inventor\n* [[Jeffrey Goldstone]]<ref>JYB 2005 p214</ref>\n* [[Ian Grant]]<ref>JYB 2005 p214</ref>\n* Sir [[Peter Hirsch]], physicist<ref>JYB 2005 p213, 214</ref>\n* [[Herbert Huppert]], 1987<ref>JYB 2005 p214</ref>\n* [[Brian David Josephson]],<ref name=\"jewishvirtuallibrary1\"/> physicist, 1973 Nobel Prize \n* [[George Kalmus]], 1988<ref>JYB 2005 p214</ref>\n* [[Andrew Keller]]<ref>[https://archive.today/20121223075320/http://www.royalsoc.ac.uk/DServe/dserve.exe?dsqIni=Dserve.ini&dsqApp=Archive&dsqCmd=show.tcl&dsqDb=Persons&dsqPos=26&dsqSearch=((text)='jewish') ]</ref>\n* [[Olga Kennard]], crystallographer 1987<ref>JYB 2005 p214</ref>\n* [[Rudolf Kompfner]],<ref>[[Concise Dictionary of National Biography]]: \"born of Jewish parents in Vienna\"</ref> invented the [[traveling wave tube]]\n* [[Hans Kronberger (physicist)|Hans Kronberger]],<ref>Concise Dictionary of National Biography: \"born in Linz, Austria, of Jewish parents\"</ref> nuclear physicist\n* [[Nicholas Kurti]],<ref>[http://www.oup.co.uk/pdf/0-19-924108-2.pdf ]{{dead link|date=January 2016}}</ref> physicist, Vice-President of the Royal Society 1965-67  <ref>Oxford [[Dictionary of National Biography]]: \"study at the university was open to him, despite being a Jew ... Kurti became a naturalized British citizen just before the outbreak of the Second World War\"</ref>\n* [[Frederick Lindemann, 1st Viscount Cherwell]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://jewish-sci-tech-books.com/personalities.htm |accessdate=16 November 2006 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061019155142/http://www.jewish-sci-tech-books.com/personalities.htm |archivedate=19 October 2006 }}</ref> physicist and politician\n* [[Henry Lipson]]<ref>JYB 1990 p201</ref>\n* Sir [[Ben Lockspeiser]]<ref>JYB 1990 p201</ref>\n* [[Stanley Mandelstam]]<ref>JYB 2005 p214</ref>\n* [[Kurt Mendelssohn]]<ref>[[