uda') ]</ref> first Jewish FRS, elected 1727\n* [[John Vane]],<ref name=\"jinfo2\"/> pharmacologist, 1982 Nobel Prize (Jewish father)\n* [[Lawrence Weiskrantz]], psychologist<ref>JYB 2005 p214</ref>\n* [[Robert Winston|Robert Winston, Baron Winston]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fortunecity.com/emachines/e11/86/helphand.html |accessdate=16 November 2006 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060903155300/http://www.fortunecity.com/emachines/e11/86/helphand.html |archivedate=3 September 2006 }}</ref> fertility expert and broadcaster\n* [[Lewis Wolpert]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sciencenet.org.uk/careers/bio/wolpert.html |accessdate=16 November 2006 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20050906064332/http://www.sciencenet.org.uk/careers/bio/wolpert.html |archivedate=6 September 2005 }}</ref> developmental biologist and broadcaster\n* [[John Yudkin]], physiologist and nutritionist\n* Lord [[Solly Zuckerman]], anatomist, evolutionist<ref>JYB 1965 p214</ref>\n\n==Mathematicians and statisticians==\n* [[Abraham Manie Adelstein]],<ref name=\"natbio\">article in Oxford [[Dictionary of National Biography]]</ref> statistician\n* [[Hertha Ayrton]],<ref name=\"natbio\"/> mathematician and engineer\n* [[Laurence Baxter]], statistician<ref>Death notices in ''[[Jewish Chronicle]]'', 15 November 1996 p 31; confirms Sidney Hart was his uncle</ref>\n* [[Abram Besicovitch]],<ref>{{cite web|author=JINFO |url=http://www.jinfo.org/Mathematics_Comp.html |title=Jewish Mathematicians |website=Jinfo.org |date=1965-10-08 |accessdate=2016-01-22}}</ref> Russian-born British mathematician (karaite)\n* [[Selig Brodetsky]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www-history.mcs.st-and.ac.uk/history//Biographies/Brodetsky.html |title=Brodetsky biography |website=History.mcs.st-and.ac.uk |date= |accessdate=2016-01-22}}</ref> mathematician, President of the Board of Deputies of British Jews, and President of the [[Hebrew University of Jerusalem]]\n* [[Jacob Bronowsk